      • mainMenu

        public void mainMenu()
        Prints the functions the program offers, from which the user can pick entering a number.
        Post:The functions are printed, and the user either is taken to another menu, or receives a message indicating he entered a wrong number.

      • addWasteMenu

        public void addWasteMenu(int version,
                         java.lang.String productIdentifier)
        Prints the indications for creating a waste and reads all the attributes of a waste, given by the user.
        Post:A message showing the successfulness of the process of creation, or one notyifing that an error occurred.
        Parameters:
        version - Integer number. Decides if certain instructions are going to be followed. 0 for a procedure of waste then product, 1 for when it comes from a procedure of product then wastes.
        productIdentifier - String with a product's identifier number. Used when version is 1.

      • addProductMenu

        public void addProductMenu(int version,
                           java.lang.String wasteIdentifier)
        Prints the indications for creating a product and reads all the attributes of a product, given by the user.
        Post: A message showing the successfulness of the process of creation, or one notyifing that an error occurred.
        Parameters:
        version - Integer number. Decides if certain instructions are going to be followed. 0 for a procedure of product then wastes, 1 for when it comes from a procedure of waste then product.
        wasteIdentifier - String with a waste's identifier number. Used when version is 1.

      • wasteInformationMenu

        public void wasteInformationMenu()
        Reads a waste's name then show that waste's complete information, product included.
        Post:Prints the information of a waste or a message notyifing the non-existence of said waste.

      • listMenu

        public void listMenu()
        Prints the 3 different options of lists. If it's the "Wastes of a product" option, it reads the desired product's identifier number.
        Post: All the wastes, products, or wastes of a product are printed, or a message notifying the non-existence of said product is printed if in "Wastes of a product" option.

      • nocivityMenu

        public void nocivityMenu()
        Reads a waste's name, then prints the nocivity of that waste.
        Post:A message with either the nocivity of the waste or notifying the non-existence of said waste is printed.

      • usabilityMenu

        public void usabilityMenu()
        Reads a waste's name, then prints wether the waste is usable or not.
        Post:The usability or not usability of the waste is printed, or a message notifying the non-existence of a product.

      • askForProduct

        public void askForProduct(java.lang.String wasteIdentifier)
        Reads wether the user wants to add an already existent product, or if he wants to create a new one.
        Post:A product is added to a waste.
        Parameters:
        wasteIdentifier - The identifier number of the waste that's being created.

      • askForWaste

        public void askForWaste(java.lang.String productIdentifier)
        Reads if the user wants to create waste for a product or not.
        Post:A waste or wastes are added to a product or not.
        Parameters:
        productIdentifier - The identifier number of the product previously created.

      • init
